lead_paragraph: Kevin Bieksa and Ryan Kesler each scored a power-play goal, and the Anaheim Ducks earned at least one point for the sixth consecutive game with a 4-1 win over the Winnipeg Jets on Sunday night.

headline.print_headline: Bieksa, Kesler Score on Power Play; Ducks Beat Jets 4-1
